## Total sales
Total sales = Total revenue - GST paid

Total sales = ₹48,85,631.54 + ₹57,622 - ₹66,822.70 = ₹48,76,430.84

---

## Advanced tax calculation

As per section 44ADA, we can take 50% of sales as income,

Net income = 50% of sales
4876430.84 X 0.5 = **₹24,38,215.42**

Income from bank interest = ₹9,119 + ₹10,860 + ₹9,165 + ₹11,000 (Assumption for March 2022) = ₹40,144

After 80C deduction,

₹24,38,215.42 -  ₹1,50,000 = ₹22,88,215.42

After [80TTA](https://cleartax.in/s/claiming-deduction-on-interest-under-section-80tta),

₹22,88,215.42 - ₹10,000 = ₹22,78,215.42
